<paragraph id="8BF97702FFC3056F7CD3F299FD81FADC" blockId="4.[166,1226,1109,1840]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">
Bionomics. 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7D8CF299FE00FB43" authority="Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya, 2018" authorityName="Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya" authorityYear="2018" box="[388,504,1237,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jukkai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7D8CF299FE00FB43" box="[388,504,1237,1263]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">M. jukkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201166BFFC3056F7E0BF299FDBCFB5C" box="[515,580,1237,1264]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most likely an univoltine species with adult flying during the early-summer phenological period (mid-May to mid-June). The new species was collected at light in mixed fescue-feather-grass steppe in SE 
<collectingCountry id="F3513792FFC3056F7FBEF359FBEEFA9C" box="[950,1046,1301,1328]" name="Ukraine" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="137D6B87FFC3056F782FF359FB9FFA9C" box="[1063,1127,1301,1328]" captionStart="Figs 5–6" captionStartId="3.[178,217,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[178,1232,871,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-413@3.[178,858,871,1741]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–6. Habitats of Multicoloria jukkai Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya, sp. n.: 5 —“Kamyani Mohyly” Nature Reserve, SE Ukraine (photo A.Zhakov); 6 — Charyn River Canyon, SE Kazakhstan (photo K. Nupponen)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404220/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">FIg. 5</figureCitation>
) and in steep river canyon with rocky slopes on both sides in SE 
<collectingCountry id="F3513792FFC3056F7F3CF379FC45FAFC" box="[820,957,1333,1360]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="137D6B87FFC3056F7FC1F379FBFFFAFC" box="[969,1031,1333,1360]" captionStart="Figs 5–6" captionStartId="3.[178,217,1757,1779]" captionTargetBox="[178,1232,871,1834]" captionTargetId="figure-413@3.[178,858,871,1741]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 5–6. Habitats of Multicoloria jukkai Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya, sp. n.: 5 —“Kamyani Mohyly” Nature Reserve, SE Ukraine (photo A.Zhakov); 6 — Charyn River Canyon, SE Kazakhstan (photo K. Nupponen)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404220/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">FIg. 6</figureCitation>
). Host plant and other aspects of bionomy are unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF97702FFC3056F7CD3F339FD68FA3C" blockId="4.[166,1226,1109,1840]" box="[219,656,1397,1424]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">C a s e o f m a t u r e l a r v a. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF97702FFC3056F7CD3F3D9FEEEFA5C" blockId="4.[166,1226,1109,1840]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. The species is known from Charyn valley (south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3513792FFC3056F783EF3D9FB39FA1C" box="[1078,1217,1429,1456]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
) and “Kamyani Mohyly” Nature Reserve (south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F3513792FFC3056F7F2BF3F9FC7EFA7C" box="[803,902,1461,1488]" name="Ukraine" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4982B9E0FFC3056F7F86F3F9FC09FA7C" box="[910,1009,1461,1488]" country="Ukraine" name="Donets'k" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Donetsk</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="4982B9E0FFC3056F782FF3F9FB31FA7C" box="[1063,1225,1461,1488]" country="Ukraine" name="Zaporizhzhya" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Zaporizhzhya</collectingRegion>
Regions).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF97702FFC3056F7CD3F3B9FDDCF89C" blockId="4.[166,1226,1109,1840]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">
Diagnosis. According to classiFIcation by S. J. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD70AF3FFC3056F7EF0F3B9FC6FF9BC" author="Reznik, S. J." box="[760,919,1525,1552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" pagination="78 - 88" refId="ref4943" refString="Reznik, S. J. 1977. A short review of the genus Multicoloria Cap. (Lepidoptera, Coleophoridae). Systematics and faunistics of insects. Leningrad, 78 - 88 [In Russian]." type="book chapter" year="1977">Reznik (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7CDAF059FEB7F983" baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[210,335,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscociliella">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7CDAF059FEB7F983" box="[210,335,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">fuscociliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7D68F059FE19F983" box="[352,481,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">medicaginis</emphasis>
)-section of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7E9CF059FCE4F983" authorityName="Capuse" authorityYear="1973" box="[660,796,1557,1583]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7E9CF059FCE4F983" box="[660,796,1557,1583]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Multicoloria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-genus and is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7889F059FDEFF9FC" authority="(Zeller, 1849)" baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1849" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscociliella">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7889F059FE8EF9E3" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">Multicoloria fuscociliella</emphasis>
(Zeller, 1849)
</taxonomicName>
. Externally, a new species well differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F780DF079FB52F9E3" baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[1029,1194,1589,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscociliella">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F780DF079FBE6F9E2" box="[1029,1054,1589,1614]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7825F079FB52F9E3" box="[1069,1194,1589,1615]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">fuscociliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the larger size and lighter coloration of both pairs of wings. In the male genitalia 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7810F019FB7BF9C3" authority="Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya, 2018" authorityName="Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya" authorityYear="2018" box="[1048,1155,1621,1647]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jukkai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7810F019FB7BF9C3" box="[1048,1155,1621,1647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">M. jukkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201166BFFC3056F7880F019FB3BF9DC" box="[1160,1219,1621,1648]" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, unlike 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7CF9F039FE69F923" baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[241,401,1653,1680]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscociliella">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7CF9F039FEF2F922" box="[241,266,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7D1DF039FE69F923" box="[277,401,1653,1679]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">fuscociliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has wider gnathos, the shorter cucullus, and, especially, much more longer terminal process of sacculus and considerably longer cornutus.The female genitalia 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7832F0D9FB5DF903" authority="Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya, 2018" authorityName="Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya" authorityYear="2018" box="[1082,1189,1685,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jukkai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7832F0D9FB5DF903" box="[1082,1189,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">M. jukkai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A201166BFFC3056F78A1F0D9FF44F97C" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC3056F7DAEF0F9FDB2F963" baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1849" box="[422,586,1717,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" genus="Multicoloria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscociliella">
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7DAEF0F9FE47F962" box="[422,447,1717,1742]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B932AB10FFC3056F7DC5F0F9FDB2F963" box="[461,586,1717,1743]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="119">fuscociliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the papillae analis more rounded apically, the thinner and longer apophyses posteriores, the much wider cup-shaped ostium, the presence a well sclerotized funnel-shaped antrum, the considerably longer spiny plot and central bent of the ductus bursa, and in much larger signum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF97702FFC2056E7CEBF6E3FB88FF46" blockId="5.[174,1232,175,234]" pageId="5" pageNumber="120">
Etymology. The new species is named in the honor of Mr. Jukka Tabell (Hartola, 
<collectingCountry id="F3513792FFC2056E7CA6F683FEF5FF46" box="[174,269,207,234]" name="Finland" pageId="5" pageNumber="120">Finland</collectingCountry>
), one of the leading specialists for the family 
<taxonomicName id="4C460C81FFC2056E7F13F683FC32FF46" authorityName="Budashkin &amp; Bidzilya" authorityYear="2018" box="[795,970,207,234]" class="Insecta" family="Coleophoridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Coleophoridae</taxonomicName>
in the World.
</paragraph>
